GitHub introduces new features for managing repository quite frequently.
Now it has a lot of helpful features to speedup the development process.

Branch-rpotection: CI + required review.
Reviewer has write access but can't merge without ARC review.

Author Create PR (TODO: title, description)
Author or robot assigns architect for task
Architect checks if PR is valid, if not reject it. If valid, enables auto-merge with squash from PR description and title,
requests review from reviewers, assign responsible reviewer.
Reviewer requests changes, author fixes them.
When CI passes and reviewer approves PR, it's merge automatically, since ARC approved it previosly.
